All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AND
The `AND` gate class represents a logical AND gate, which returns true if and only if all of its inputs are true.
BasicGate
Represents a basic logic gate with multiple inputs and a single output.
BasicPassThrough
Represents a basic pass through with a single input and a single output.
BasicReceiver
An abstract class that represents a basic receiver with a single input and no outputs.

Represents a button that a user can press.

The `Delay` class represents a logical element that adds a set amount of delay to the signal that travels through it.

NAND
The `NAND` gate class represents a logical NAND gate, which returns false if and only if all of its inputs are true.
NOR
The `NOR` gate class represents a logical NOR gate, which returns false if any of its inputs are true.
NOT
The 'NOT' class represents a logical NOT gate, which returns true if the number of true inputs is odd and false otherwise.
OR
The `OR` gate class represents a logical OR gate, which returns true if any of its inputs are true.
